summary: Deneth - former Arch-Mage of the College of Winterhold\'s personal pocket dimension. Adds player housing in the form of ruins built on floating chunks of ice floating in an endless void (See screenshots). Includes a teleportation spell to get you in, exit through the main gate takes you back to point of casting.
descriptionHtml:
Deneth\'s Study
Made by Seronalis

==============

Arch-Mage during the Great Collapse Deneth sought a place away from the college to spend time. After much research he created a spell to teleport himself to his own private pocket dimension. It became his \"private study\" and as he aged he spent more and more time in seclusion. Soon the Study became his home.

After his death the details of his great achievement were lost. Never having told anyone the secrets of his realm it was thought inaccessible. With out tending the dimension started a slow decay, breaking a part and floating aimlessly into the void. Rumors persist that before his death he made a copy of the spell, though no one knows where it may be if it exists at all.

==============

Features:
A personal pocket dimension to call home
A spell to enter from any location, with return to point of casting

Furniture
1 Alchemy Workstation
1 Anvil
1 Bed
10 Bookshelves
5 Chests
1 Enchanting Workstation
1 Grindstone
1 Tanning Rack
1 Wardrobe
1 Workbench

==============
